'''华盛顿纪念碑综合征'''（Washington Monument Syndrome），也被称为'''拉什莫尔山综合征'''<ref name=Ferrell>{{cite news|first=David|last=Ferrell|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=Library Book Liberation Front: Don't Tax Library Books|url=http://www.laweekly.com/news/news/library-book-liberation-front-dont-tax-library-books/18796/|newspaper=[[LA_Weekly|LA Weekly]]|date=30 April 2008|accessdate=9 May 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080510104510/http://www.laweekly.com/news/news/library-book-liberation-front-dont-tax-library-books/18796/|archivedate=2008年5月10日}}</ref>或'''消防员优先原则'''<ref name=Peters>{{cite news|title=The Firemen First Principle|first=Charles|last=Peters|authorlink=Charles Peters|url=http://www.unz.org/Pub/WashingtonMonthly-1976mar-00008?View=PDFPages|newspaper=[[Washington_Monthly|Washington Monthly]]|date=March 1976|accessdate=18 February 2013|archive-date=2013-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215416/http://www.unz.org/Pub/WashingtonMonthly-1976mar-00008?View=PDFPages|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The Nightmare of Sequestration Hits Home|first=James|last=Fallows|authorlink=James Fallows|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2013/02/the-nightmare-of-sequestration-hits-home/273260/|newspaper=[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]]|date=18 February 2013|accessdate=18 February 2013|archive-date=2013-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213549/http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2013/02/the-nightmare-of-sequestration-hits-home/273260/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是[[美国政府|美国政府]]应对削减预算和[[美国政府停摆|政府停摆]]的一种政治[[策略|策略]]。该策略是优先关闭与民众贴近、受民众欢迎的政府服务，如[[国家公园|国家公园]]和[[图书馆|图书馆]]，让[[教师|教师]]和[[消防员|消防员]]停工。这样让民众感受到停摆的切肤之痛，更利于通过[[增税|增税]]法案。[[华盛顿纪念碑|华盛顿纪念碑]]和[[拉什莫尔山|拉什莫尔山]]国家公园是很受欢迎的景点，所以一般都会在停摆中被关闭，这也是本策略名称的来源。<ref>{{cite news|first=John S.|last=Gardner|title=Condomania|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/comment/gardner200604120721.asp|newspaper=[[National_Review|National Review]]|date=12 April 2006|accessdate=9 May 2008|archive-date=2009-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090214113117/http://www.nationalreview.com/comment/gardner200604120721.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref>National Review杂志认为这种策略可以和绑架、敲诈相提并论。<ref>{{cite news|first=Wendell|last=Cox|authorlink=Wendell Cox|title=Blackmail Strategy|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/comment/comment-cox062502.asp|newspaper=National Review|date=25 June 2002|accessdate=9 May 2008|archive-date=2008-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513193247/http://www.nationalreview.com/comment/comment-cox062502.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref>

本策略的主要目的是让选民体会到政府机构不可或缺。相似的手段也曾被作用于立法者。1970年代[[美国铁路公司|美国铁路公司]]被削减预算的时候就曾停运了开往一些[[国会议员|国会议员]]家乡的线路。<ref name=Peters/>

1969年政府停摆的时候，国家公园管理者小乔治·哈佐格首次关闭了受欢迎的华盛顿纪念碑和[[大峡谷国家公园|大峡谷国家公园]]，这一做法被称为“华盛顿纪念碑综合征”，遭到民众的批评，小乔治·哈佐格也因此被解雇。<ref>{{cite web |last=Kennedy |first=Shirley Duglin |title=The Washington Monument Syndrome |url=http://www.allbusiness.com/media-telecommunications/information-services-libraries/12300846-1.html |work=Information Today |accessdate=24 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713004910/http://www.allbusiness.com/media-telecommunications/information-services-libraries/12300846-1.html |archivedate=2011-07-13 |date=2009-04-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

